President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed March 2017 as American Red Cross Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the incredible work of the organization in assisting hundreds of thousands of Americans affected by disasters each year. The Red Cross responded to 180 significant incidents in 2016, providing emergency shelters, meals, and relief items. They also helped 79,000 families recover from home fires. President Trump emphasizes the importance of volunteers and the support of the American people for the Red Cross to continue its vital national and international roles. He encourages all Americans to observe this month by supporting the work of service and relief organizations.